<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-10 02:10 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6652 &Cx1f; tic-z
r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-CARDINALS-VIKINGS     01-10 0958
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDINALS-VIKINGS-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`MR. BEIGE' USES UNDERDOG ROLE AS MOTIVATION 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS _ Unlike the Cardinals' owner, he never was a
waterboy. Unlike his quarterback, he doesn't quote from ``The
Waterboy''.
</P>
<P>
   But as his team continues to shock the world, Mr. Beige is
becoming a master motivator.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm sure there are a lot of smiles in Minnesota right now,''
Cardinals Coach Vince Tobin told the team seconds after their
first-round playoff victory over Dallas eight days ago.
</P>
<P>
   ``They don't have to play San Francisco or Green Bay. They get
to play the lowly Cardinals.''
</P>
<P>
   Few think the ``lowly'' Cardinals, 16-point underdogs, have a
chance to upset the Minnesota Vikings today in an NFC second-round
playoff game at the Metrodome.
</P>
<P>
   A Minneapolis newspaper said the Cardinals are as dangerous as a
``ball of lint.'' A St. Paul, Minn., newspaper already is talking
about the Vikings' ``March to Miami'' and Super Bowl XXXIII. A Twin
Cities radio station asked its listeners Friday whom they thought
the Vikings will play in the Super Bowl, Denver or the New York
Jets.
</P>
<P>
   None of that fazes Cardinals quarterback Jake Plummer, who keeps
repeating a line from the movie ``Waterboy''.
</P>
<P>
   ``We can do it,'' Plummer said. ``We can do it.''
</P>
<P>
   Only one team did beat the Vikings, who were an NFL best 15-1 in
the regular season.
</P>
<P>
   The Tampa Bay Buccaneers stunned them, 27-24, on Nov. 1 at
Tampa's Raymond James Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Tampa scored first and trailed only once. Mike Alstott rushed
for 128 yards in that game, and Warrick Dunn added 115. The
Cardinals haven't had two 100-yard rushers in a game all season.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've got to be successful running the ball,'' said the
Cardinals' Adrian Murrell, their 1,000-yard rusher.
</P>
<P>
   The Vikings have the NFL's top passer in Randall Cunningham.
Rookie Randy Moss had a league-high 17 touchdown catches. John
Randle led all defensive tackles in sacks with 10{.
</P>
<P>
   Cardinals defensive end Simeon Rice said Vikings offensive
tackles Todd Steussie and Korey Stringer are the best duo he has
seen all season.
</P>
<P>
   ``One thing you can't do is fall behind early,'' Buccaneers
Coach Tony Dungy said. ``The first time we played them, we got
behind, 21-0, and lost, 31-7. When we beat them, we were one of the
few teams still in the game in the fourth quarter.''
</P>
<P>
   The Vikings set an NFL scoring record with 556 points, and their
past seven opponents have been beaten by 10 or more points.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a team that has so many ways to beat you,'' Dungy said.
``Everyone says you don't want to give up the big play early, and
then Moss catches a 60-yard touchdown on you. They have a back
(Robert Smith) who averages 5 yards a carry and another one (Leroy
Hoard) who comes in the game and runs over people.
</P>
<P>
   ``You know they're going to make their share of plays. You know
they're going to score. You just hope to make them go six plays to
get down the field instead of three.''
</P>
<P>
   The Cardinals know they can't get into a shootout with
Minnesota. They also don't think the Vikings are going to dominate
a Cardinals defense that shut out Dallas a week ago until the final
four minutes.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think our offense is going to have to go out and score
45 to 70 points,'' Cardinals wide receiver Frank Sanders said. ``I
mean, this is not a (Brigham Young)-San Diego State game. We
believe our defense can shut them down. We really do.''
</P>
<P>
   Few agree with Sanders.
</P>
<P>
   The Vikings were unbeaten at home this season and won those
games by an average of more than 23 points.
</P>
<P>
   They have nine players who will be in the Pro Bowl. The
Cardinals' only representative is Aeneas Williams, the only
cornerback on the team Moss thinks is better than average.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think there is a tremendous amount of pressure on them,''
Cardinals offensive tackle Lomas Brown said. ``Compiling a 15-1
record and all the offensive records they broke, anything short of
a Super Bowl for them is a failure.''
</P>
<P>
   Vikings Coach Dennis Green thinks there is no chance his team
will overlook the Cardinals, who needed field goals from Chris
Jacke on the final plays of their last three regular-season games
to qualify for the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   ``Many of the same people that say we're the favorites were the
same people who picked us fourth in the NFC Central Division,''
Green said. ``It was only five months ago that they said Green Bay
would win it, Tampa Bay would be second, Detroit third and
Minnesota fourth. We saw ourselves as the Central Division champion
then and we see ourselves as that now.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've never been privy to what people think conventional
wisdom is. We're playing just as hard as we have for the previous
16 games and doing everything we can to win.''
</P>
<P>
   A Cardinals victory today would be one of the biggest upsets in
NFL playoff history. It would put former waterboy Bill Bidwill's
franchise, which hadn't won a playoff game in 51 years until a week
ago, one step away from the Super Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Cardinals defensive back J.J. McCleskey said he doesn't think an
upset would be shocking.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is not the NBA championship,'' McCleskey said. ``It's not
the best four out of seven. It's whoever shows up that day. We're
good enough to show up (today).''
</P>
<P>
   ``Nobody in this locker room feels we're going to lose,'' Jamir
Miller said. ``Cinderella was a girl who had a fairy godmother who
came to give her something. Nothing was given to us, and I want
people to understand that. There's no Cinderella to this, there's
no mystery to it.
</P>
<P>
   ``We won the games we needed to win to get where we are. So
that's what it boils down to _ we worked hard to get it, and we got
it.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-10-99 0210EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990110.0020 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-10 02:13 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6653 &Cx1f; tic-z
