<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDINALS-DEFENSE-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`WE MATCH UP FINE'  
 MCGINNIS SAYS CARDS UP TO TASK 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By LEE SHAPPELL  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS _ Whether the Minnesota Vikings have the best
offense of all time is debatable. What is certain is that no team
ever scored more points in a season than the Vikings just did.
</P>
<P>
   Their lowest scoring games were 24 points, twice, en route to an
NFL-record 556.
</P>
<P>
   ``You don't stop them,'' said Dave McGinnis, the Cardinals
defensive coordinator, who is rumored to be the leading candidate
for the Chicago Bears' head coaching position.
</P>
<P>
   But McGinnis is being asked to slow them enough to give the
Cardinals' offense a chance to score more when they meet in the
second round of the NFL playoffs at the Metrodome today .
</P>
<P>
   One statistic lost in the hoopla over the high-scoring Vikings
is that the Cardinals' defense, the youngest overall in the NFL,
has surrendered only one touchdown in each of its past three games
and only five in its past four games.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've gone out and made our mark,'' said outside linebacker
Jamir Miller. ``We've shown that we can play with anybody. We've
gotten stronger and stronger at the most important time. That shows
the character of this team. We're composed of winners, not
quitters. Minnesota has a great offense, but we've got a great
defense, too.''
</P>
<P>
   Miller made 12 tackles and had two sacks last week in a 20-7
drubbing of the Dallas Cowboys. Five-time Pro Bowl cornerback
Aeneas Williams intercepted two passes. Rookie corner Corey Chavous
knocked down five passes. Ends Simeon Rice and Andre Wadsworth and
tackle Mark Smith controlled the run and pressured Troy Aikman.
</P>
<P>
   The Vikings are younger and more athletic than the Cowboys, but
even McGinnis said, ``We match up fine.'' He came up with a scheme
that all but smothered the Cowboys in the playoff opener, losing a
shutout with 3:33 remaining only after a long punt return left the
Cowboys a short field to negotiate.
</P>
<P>
   ``Last week is gone,'' McGinnis said. ``We've got to get a game
plan together for this week, and we've done that. I was in the NFC
Central for 10 years. I've been in the Metrodome a lot. It is a
loud place. The way you take the crowd out of the game is to play
well.''
</P>
<P>
   Figuring a way to take Randall Cunningham, the NFL's top-rated
passer at 106.0 points, out of the game is a more complex issue.
Even at age 35, Cunningham is mobile. Pro Bowl receivers Cris
Carter and Randy Moss enabled Cunningham to fire 34 touchdown
passes, second only to 36 by Steve Young of San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously we have a real challenge out there this week with
the receivers and the offense that we're playing,'' said Larry
Marmie, the Cardinals defensive backs coach. ``I don't know whether
it's an acid test. Aeneas Williams has played against a lot of
great receivers over the years. Certainly Randy Moss is a very
talented guy, but Aeneas takes anybody he goes against as a
challenge. It doesn't matter who it is.''
</P>
<P>
   As Coach Vince Tobin points out, the Vikings also have made big
plays rushing, too, with Robert Smith gaining for 1,187 yards,
fifth in the NFC.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know that you stop a team such as that,'' Tobin said.
``You can control it, keep it from getting big plays. They've got
an awful lot of them by running, throwing it both short and deep,
throwing screens that have gone long. They've got a lot of
weapons.''
</P>
<P>
   But so do the Cardinals defenders.
</P>
<P>
   ``Our attitude the whole year has been `We've got to have it,'
'' said safety Tommy Bennett. ``You've got to play the same every
game, every down. That's the reason we are where we are. That's
part of our maturity. Two years ago we had the talent, but we
didn't have the maturity. Same last year, when we couldn't finish
all those close games. This year we finally came together, and
we're still a young team. That youthful energy has been a plus for
us this year.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have a really good game plan for these guys. We can compete
with them.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-10-99 0222EST &QL; 
