<P>
   WB-TIME-WARNER (Pasadena, Calif.) _ Along with much of the
audience and most of the profits, the confidence bordering on
arrogance that once characterized the network television business
has faded away this season. But it is alive and well in at least
one place, television's youngest, hippest and increasingly its only
upwardly mobile address: the upstart would-be network known as WB.
By Bill Carter.
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 7 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Bottom center)
</P>
