r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GEN-HOFFARTH-COLUMN-L     01-10 0667
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GEN-HOFFARTH-COLUMN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IT'S A BLACK-EYE OPTIONAL AFFAIR
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Dear friend:
</P>
<P>
   A belated New Year's greeting to all! Best wishes for a safe and
healthy 1999.
</P>
<P>
   It's been a busy time for all of us, what with parole and
commission hearings, psychological examinations and
community-service work. But Saturday night is a special night for
me, my family and my new entourage.
</P>
<P>
   At the Las Vegas Hilton Hotel and Casino, we request the honor
of your presence as I have been allowed to once again return to
some economic stability and exploit myself for others by beating
the living daylights out of another human being.
</P>
<P>
   Please share with us in this special pugilistic moment either in
person or through the magic of pay-per-view television.
</P>
<P>
   In lieu of an RSVP, please purchase a guest favor at the
entrance. Cocktail reception begins at five o'clock with the main
course _ a filet of Francois Botha _ expected to begin at about
eight o'clock in the evening. Reception to follow at the home of
Siegfried and Roy and/or Las Vegas Memorial Hospital emergency
ward.
</P>
<P>
   I look forward to seeing you there and anticipate an evening you
might not soon forget. Keep your ears open for further details.
</P>
<P>
   Sincerely,
</P>
<P>
   M. Tyson, esq.
</P>
<P>
   (Now repeat all that aloud with your best Mike Tyson imitation.)
</P>
<P>
   So where was Milwaukee Bucks owner Herb Kohl when this NBA
lockout deal had to be approved last week?
</P>
<P>
   Oh....
</P>
<P>
   The U.S. senator from Wisconsin was being sworn in as a witness
in President Clinton's impeachment trial.
</P>
<P>
   Now you see what an unnecessary burden this puts on everyone?...
</P>
<P>
   Let's figure this out: Michael Jordan is supposedly holed up in
a $25,000-a-night hotel suite in the Bahamas while his NBA
counterparts scrape together to make ends meet during the final
days of the lockout.
</P>
<P>
   Big spender? It's all relative.
</P>
<P>
   Considering he made $30 million a year on just last year's
Chicago Bulls paychecks, then the equivalent for someone making
$50,000 a year would be to stay in a $41.67-a-night Worst Western
Motel. Do the math....
</P>
<P>
   A Jay Leno quip on the NBA situation: ``The lockout hurt the
little people. I'm glad Bob Costas is back to work.''...
</P>
<P>
   Eddie Jones and draft picks for Scottie Pippen makes a lotta
cents....
</P>
<P>
   NBC already has plans to have the casts of ``Friends'' and
``ER'' do promos for the return of NBA programming....
</P>
<P>
   Paging James Earl Jones. You're wanted on the set for ``The John
Thompson Story.''...
</P>
<P>
   Load the boys up in the pickup for ``Varsity Blues,'' which
comes out Friday. Think of it as ``All The Right Moves'' meets
``Dawson's Creek,'' with a bunch of ``North Dallas Forty'' thrown
in for excitement....
</P>
<P>
   Just when you think L.A. doesn't need an NFL franchise, Playboy
comes out with an issue featuring bare, naked cheerleaders. Based
on this February issue, a Denver-Atlanta Super Bowl would be most
appealing....
</P>
